               <msContents>
                  <summary>F<locus target="#1r"/>-214v: Psalter. The midpoint of the Psalms (75v) is unmarked. Psalm 151 is the long version. The fourth biblical canticle is Prayer of Hana, Mother of Samuel, prophet. The Song of Songs contains the Hebraic edition. The Praises of Mary begins on Monday and culminates on Sunday. F<locus target="#215r"/>-217v: The Angels Praise Her. Notes. With fine materials and harags from the Government scriptorium. The Praises of Mary has a harag for each day of the week. Illuminations: <locus target="#182v"/>: A very fine and full-color illumination of Mary and her beloved Son. F. vi v(erso) a very fine full-color illumination of David Playing the Harp.There are also several pencil drawings: i v(erso): David playing the harp. ii r(ecto): harag. ii v(erso): harag. 219r: harag. 219v: An Equestrian Saint. 220r: Horse and rider. 224v: a horse. </summary>
